countValues

public int countValues(String firstKeyValue)
                throws ValueInvalidException
Returns the number of values a SUBPAGES key can expect based upon the first value that key has. The subpages key is special because the FROM value also expects two more values after it. This function is used when parsing a stream of parameters.

Specified by:
